<br>
Soya, Lizie or Liziie.<br>
<br>
I've tried to organize this in such a way as to give someone an idea, of what &quot;Cost of Materials&quot; really means when buying a weapon or shield from a guild crafter. Hope it helps.<br>
<br>
Keep in mind that these are approximate costs for SINGLE attempts at creating a weapon or shield.  One attempt might not yield the 98% + quality item you're looking for. With the last patch I'm seeing much higher quality weapons on average.<br>
<br>
The typical range for me is 94% to 97% quality when fiddling around with materials that still give me skill.<br>
96% to 99% for materials that are below my learning range. <br>
&lt;&lt;&lt; 100% quality is RARE &gt;&gt;&gt;<br>
<br>
I currently have 618 in weapon crafting. I'm able to create; Mithril,Fine alloy,alloy, steel, iron and &lt;snickers&gt; Bronze weapons.<br>
Wood,metal and leather 615 +/-<br>
<br>
I'm able to salvage 25th level weapons and below if you'd like to clear out a lil vault space and make some coin in the process.<br>
<br>
Questions, concerns, comments... or orders. Please give me a tell in game or reply to this post. Thank you.<br>
